"osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "I also have no experience with docker. IMO the competition should provide an image and directions on how to add our software to make it run.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I also have no experience with docker. IMO the competition should provide an image and directions on how to add our software to make it run.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-20T03:09:18.372173+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Rud Merriam", "uuid": "{79efa10c-b8b6-4b55-9d05-7d0057e235cb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B79efa10c-b8b6-4b55-9d05-7d0057e235cb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B79efa10c-b8b6-4b55-9d05-7d0057e235cb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:c6ed1bc6-3112-49ac-9453-b3846fe562dc/5c7bde69-befb-417b-9aae-9db0c9a59777/128"}}, "nickname": "rmerriam", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:c6ed1bc6-3112-49ac-9453-b3846fe562dc"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 36084339}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/36085243.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-36085243"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "The decision to use Docker has me baffled.  We will be running on Amazon AWS EC2 servers for practice and it only takes a couple clicks to save an image there.  That image is easily loaded into a new EC2 instance.  And we're done.  There really is no need for all of us to learn to build Docker containers.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The decision to use Docker has me baffled.  We will be running on Amazon AWS EC2 servers for practice and it only takes a couple clicks to save an image there.  That image is easily loaded into a new EC2 instance.  And we're done.  There really is no need for all of us to learn to build Docker containers.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-20T04:45:02.132683+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "dan", "uuid": "{a93bd0ec-35fc-49a5-aa8a-b0b57403c2d0}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Ba93bd0ec-35fc-49a5-aa8a-b0b57403c2d0%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Ba93bd0ec-35fc-49a5-aa8a-b0b57403c2d0%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/dd56d3105d7602d83d5c35a320f6b36cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsD-6.png"}}, "nickname": "dan77062", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e0e36946-cb60-4776-8f47-2e9a0285ad35"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 36085243}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/36105604.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-36105604"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "There's more that goes into the EC2 instance than just team code. We're working on an example and tutorial for the docker setup.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>There's more that goes into the EC2 instance than just team code. We're working on an example and tutorial for the docker setup.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-20T17:19:29.934958+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 36105604}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/36105656.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-36105656"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "thanks because I could not find (in my 30 minutes of research last night) a way to have a docker container use host system libraries and such. \n\nAlso getting networking into a docker container is easy, but getting it out to the host system (communicating with gazebo) looked far trickier.\n\n-aric", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>thanks because I could not find (in my 30 minutes of research last night) a way to have a docker container use host system libraries and such. </p>\n<p>Also getting networking into a docker container is easy, but getting it out to the host system (communicating with gazebo) looked far trickier.</p>\n<p>-aric</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-20T17:21:41.470430+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Aric Stewart", "uuid": "{5e392443-300d-426f-83e1-2132cd8f37b7}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5e392443-300d-426f-83e1-2132cd8f37b7%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5e392443-300d-426f-83e1-2132cd8f37b7%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:3d3a190f-08f3-4f9b-971f-f02316fcf8de/987c2161-0456-4cb1-95d3-24e3388f9feb/128"}}, "nickname": "aricstewart", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:3d3a190f-08f3-4f9b-971f-f02316fcf8de"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 36105656}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/36111843.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-36111843"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "[Louise Poubel](https://bitbucket.org/chapulina/) Of course, but in the end we will be running on Amazon EC2 machines.  So why not build an EC2 instance with whatever code needs to be there, make an image of that on amazon and make that available to the teams?  Then we create an instance with that image, add our code and we are done.  We can make an image of that and then launch as needed.  Amazon makes this really, really easy to do.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p><a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://bitbucket.org/chapulina/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Louise Poubel</a> Of course, but in the end we will be running on Amazon EC2 machines.  So why not build an EC2 instance with whatever code needs to be there, make an image of that on amazon and make that available to the teams?  Then we create an instance with that image, add our code and we are done.  We can make an image of that and then launch as needed.  Amazon makes this really, really easy to do.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-21T00:42:36.091503+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "dan", "uuid": "{a93bd0ec-35fc-49a5-aa8a-b0b57403c2d0}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Ba93bd0ec-35fc-49a5-aa8a-b0b57403c2d0%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Ba93bd0ec-35fc-49a5-aa8a-b0b57403c2d0%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/dd56d3105d7602d83d5c35a320f6b36cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsD-6.png"}}, "nickname": "dan77062", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e0e36946-cb60-4776-8f47-2e9a0285ad35"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 36111843}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/36131025.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-36131025"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "Hi @dan77062 , I understand your concerns about Docker. And I hope you understand that in order to prevent cheating, we must have control over what teams are putting into the machine. \n\nAlso keep in mind that using AMIs might be simpler for you, but that would add a requirement that all teams create AWS accounts, run instances and create AMIs.\n\nBelieve me, we're trying to follow the path of least friction for all teams.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Hi @dan77062 , I understand your concerns about Docker. And I hope you understand that in order to prevent cheating, we must have control over what teams are putting into the machine. </p>\n<p>Also keep in mind that using AMIs might be simpler for you, but that would add a requirement that all teams create AWS accounts, run instances and create AMIs.</p>\n<p>Believe me, we're trying to follow the path of least friction for all teams.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-21T16:12:42.103340+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 36131025}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/36132748.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-36132748"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "Oh, I thought that since we would be running on an AWS EC2 instance, that would mean we all had accounts and could run the instance.  In fact, I thought that part of being in Phase 2 was that each team would be given access to an amazon EC2 server.\n\nIn any case, thanks for listening to the idea and explaining in more detail the reasoning.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Oh, I thought that since we would be running on an AWS EC2 instance, that would mean we all had accounts and could run the instance.  In fact, I thought that part of being in Phase 2 was that each team would be given access to an amazon EC2 server.</p>\n<p>In any case, thanks for listening to the idea and explaining in more detail the reasoning.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-04-21T17:55:59.564850+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "dan", "uuid": "{a93bd0ec-35fc-49a5-aa8a-b0b57403c2d0}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Ba93bd0ec-35fc-49a5-aa8a-b0b57403c2d0%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Ba93bd0ec-35fc-49a5-aa8a-b0b57403c2d0%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/dd56d3105d7602d83d5c35a320f6b36cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsD-6.png"}}, "nickname": "dan77062", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e0e36946-cb60-4776-8f47-2e9a0285ad35"}, "updated_on": "2017-04-21T20:47:23.376546+00:00", "type": "issue_comment", "id": 36132748}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/37100583.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-37100583"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "Related issue #182", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Related issue <a href=\"#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/182/docker-base-image\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Docker Base Image\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#182</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-05-24T01:27:06.908992+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37100583}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/37263112.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-37263112"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "Some of these things have been addressed on other issues, but just for completeness:\n\n> Are we going to have to install the whole ros stack into our docker images in order to use them?\n\nYes, you must install everything you're going to use. \n\n> Is there a suggested baseline or stub Dockerfile that could be started from? \n\nThere is an example docker file [here](https://github.com/scpeters/src_field_computer_test) which you can take a look. \n\nI'll close this issue, please reopen if something is left to be addressed.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Some of these things have been addressed on other issues, but just for completeness:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Are we going to have to install the whole ros stack into our docker images in order to use them?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes, you must install everything you're going to use. </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is there a suggested baseline or stub Dockerfile that could be started from? </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>There is an example docker file <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://github.com/scpeters/src_field_computer_test\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a> which you can take a look. </p>\n<p>I'll close this issue, please reopen if something is left to be addressed.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-05-30T23:44:40.881027+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37263112}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/37263113.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-37263113"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": null, "markup": "markdown", "html": "", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-05-30T23:44:49.332781+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37263113}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/37297917.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-37297917"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "Note that make sure you do all your ROS package / other library installations using the Dockerfile, and not in a bash script that's run after the container is launched. This is because in the final competition, the FC docker container will not have access to the internet.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Note that make sure you do all your ROS package / other library installations using the Dockerfile, and not in a bash script that's run after the container is launched. This is because in the final competition, the FC docker container will not have access to the internet.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-05-31T23:57:00.664975+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Ian Chen", "uuid": "{eaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:10b01d41-a2e9-4a41-a907-e6e2f03b6cd5/1e4adcdf-1946-4280-9aea-eb5f15a7f912/128"}}, "nickname": "Ian Chen", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:10b01d41-a2e9-4a41-a907-e6e2f03b6cd5"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37297917}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/37298392.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-37298392"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "@iche033 Your last comment confuses me but then I am a total noob with Docker and the AWS. Let me see if I understand:\n\n1. The AWS will start\n1. The Dockerfile will be invoked - that is allowed access to the Internet to load packages and GitHub files\n1. A startup script is run.\n1. After that there is no access to the Internet for package or other uploads. \n\nI still think there is much more that SRC could include in the base image in addition to the \"FROM ros:indigo-ros-base\" that would speed the Docker setup. Everything in the scpeters dockerfile is going to be needed and probably much more. Even if teams didn't need some of it there is no cost to having it loaded.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>@iche033 Your last comment confuses me but then I am a total noob with Docker and the AWS. Let me see if I understand:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The AWS will start</li>\n<li>The Dockerfile will be invoked - that is allowed access to the Internet to load packages and GitHub files</li>\n<li>A startup script is run.</li>\n<li>After that there is no access to the Internet for package or other uploads. </li>\n</ol>\n<p>I still think there is much more that SRC could include in the base image in addition to the \"FROM ros:indigo-ros-base\" that would speed the Docker setup. Everything in the scpeters dockerfile is going to be needed and probably much more. Even if teams didn't need some of it there is no cost to having it loaded.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-01T00:34:34.540541+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Rud Merriam", "uuid": "{79efa10c-b8b6-4b55-9d05-7d0057e235cb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B79efa10c-b8b6-4b55-9d05-7d0057e235cb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B79efa10c-b8b6-4b55-9d05-7d0057e235cb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:c6ed1bc6-3112-49ac-9453-b3846fe562dc/5c7bde69-befb-417b-9aae-9db0c9a59777/128"}}, "nickname": "rmerriam", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:c6ed1bc6-3112-49ac-9453-b3846fe562dc"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37298392}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/37383689.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-37383689"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "yes, what you described is correct. Specifically, there is no access to internet from the docker container.\n\nIt takes around ~2min to build scpeters Docker image. I'll ticket an issue to provide a base docker image but given the time left, it'll likely be a lower priority task.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>yes, what you described is correct. Specifically, there is no access to internet from the docker container.</p>\n<p>It takes around ~2min to build scpeters Docker image. I'll ticket an issue to provide a base docker image but given the time left, it'll likely be a lower priority task.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-05T18:00:52.177303+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Ian Chen", "uuid": "{eaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:10b01d41-a2e9-4a41-a907-e6e2f03b6cd5/1e4adcdf-1946-4280-9aea-eb5f15a7f912/128"}}, "nickname": "Ian Chen", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:10b01d41-a2e9-4a41-a907-e6e2f03b6cd5"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37383689}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/37383901.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-37383901"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "it takes around 15-20 minutes to build the image for me . Had to add in  opencv3, scipy, cv_bridge in addition to other base packages", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>it takes around 15-20 minutes to build the image for me . Had to add in  opencv3, scipy, cv_bridge in addition to other base packages</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-05T18:15:43.184291+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Harish Balasubramaniam", "uuid": "{ae8d9dff-7ceb-444d-818f-c406b2af9f7b}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bae8d9dff-7ceb-444d-818f-c406b2af9f7b%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bae8d9dff-7ceb-444d-818f-c406b2af9f7b%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/798f0e3badbe30980acc94830642a1bbd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsHB-3.png"}}, "nickname": "harishbalasub", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cf139131-fde1-424c-8174-4b3ba865f59c"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37383901}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/37384241.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-37384241"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "Will `FROM ros:indigo-perception` work in the finals?  It avoids having to install a lot of packages piecemeal.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Will <code>FROM ros:indigo-perception</code> work in the finals?  It avoids having to install a lot of packages piecemeal.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-05T18:35:19.638906+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Phil Bolenbaugh ", "uuid": "{f4c1b4b5-67b8-454a-9736-96ecd9a40147}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bf4c1b4b5-67b8-454a-9736-96ecd9a40147%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bf4c1b4b5-67b8-454a-9736-96ecd9a40147%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3bc1dd8a06172e1c902076c1d19c9e16d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "philbevv", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:22f62cd3-c537-4ae1-b33b-252b834d3bc1"}, "updated_on": "2017-06-05T18:35:49.511736+00:00", "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37384241}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139/comments/37384858.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/139#comment-37384858"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/139.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 139, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Docker container baseline"}, "content": {"raw": "@philbevv , have you tried this on CloudSim? I don't see why it wouldn't work. The field computer is running nvidia-docker, if that was your worry.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>@philbevv , have you tried this on CloudSim? I don't see why it wouldn't work. The field computer is running nvidia-docker, if that was your worry.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-05T19:21:49.415184+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 37384858}], "page": 1, "size": 17}